criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Have had a single episode of unilateral, ischemic stroke, in middle cerebral artery
             proven by means of magnetic resonance imaging or computed tomography;

          -  Young adult individuals, aged between 18 and 60 years;

          -  Both sexes;

          -  Patients in late subacute stage. Late sub-acute stage will be considered for patients
             between 3 and 6 months after stroke;

          -  Absence of cognitive deficits, assessed using the Mini Mental State Examination (MEEM>
             24);

          -  Patients with mild to moderate degree of injury severity (NIHHS <17 points);

          -  Presentation of up to 4 points on the Rankin scale.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Use of drugs that modulate the activity of the Central Nervous System;

          -  Carriers of implanted metallic or electronic devices; cardiac pacemaker;

          -  habitual use of drugs or alcohol;

          -  Epilepsy history report; gestation; people with traumatic brain injury or tumors.
